<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - GitPlus" description="Privacy policy for GitPlus VS Code extension">
  <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);">
    <a href="/">Home</a> / <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a> / GitPlus
  </p>

  <h1>GitPlus Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);">Last Updated: December 2025</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    GitPlus is a VS Code extension that enhances local Git workflows by providing additional UI features 
    such as commit renaming and file history visualization.
  </p>

  <h2>Information Collected</h2>
  <p style="padding: var(--spacing-md); background: var(--color-border); margin: var(--spacing-md) 0;">
    <strong>GitPlus does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    All operations (renaming commits, reading Git history) happen locally on your machine, 
    using the local Git CLI.
  </p>
  <p>We do not collect:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Source code</li>
    <li>Commit content</li>
    <li>File names</li>
    <li>Usage data</li>
    <li>Personal identifiers</li>
    <li>Telemetry or analytics</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Storage</h2>
  <p>
    GitPlus stores no data. VS Code and Git themselves may store settings, logs, or cache — 
    GitPlus does not access or transmit these.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>None.</strong> No analytics, no telemetry, no remote servers.
  </p>

  <h2>Permissions</h2>
  <p>
    GitPlus requests only the minimum permissions necessary to function with VS Code's native Git integration. 
    It does not request permission to access your file system, network, or any external services.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy inquiries, contact us at:<br />
    <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:dps.manit@gmail.com">dps.manit@gmail.com</a>
  </p>

  <footer class="footer">
    <p><a href="/privacy">← Back to Master Privacy Policy</a></p>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
